{"meta":{"domain":"subjects","kid":"4769","authors":[{"fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre","id":"6"}],"title":"","dates":{"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:13:59 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:13:59 UTC"}},"nodes":[{"index":0,"parent_index":-1,"body":"<p class=\"Paragraph\">Tibetan verbs fall into two main classes: <strong>volitional verbs<\/strong> and <strong>non-volitional verbs<\/strong>. The grammar of European languages does not make this opposition between volitional and non-volitional. However, in terms of vocabulary the differentiation can be observed. For example, \u201chear\u201d and \u201csee\u201d are non-volitional, while \u201clisten\u201d and \u201clook\u201d are volitional.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">Within each of these two main classes, a distinction is made between <strong>transitive verbs <\/strong>and <strong>intransitive verbs<\/strong>. Transitive verbs require an object, whereas intransitive verbs do not.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">There are, then, altogether four basic classes of verbs: non-volitional intransitive, volitional intransitive, non-volitional transitive, and volitional transitive.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\"><strong>Table: Examples of the Four Verb Classes<\/strong><\/p><table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"> <tbody> <tr> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\">\u00a0<\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><em>Volitional<\/em><\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0fb1\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f72\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f56\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f45\u0f53\u0f0b<em>\u00a0<\/em><\/span><em>\u00a0<\/em><\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><em>Non-Volitional<\/em><\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0fb1\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f72\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f5e\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f56\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f45\u0f53\u0f0b<em>\u00a0<\/em><\/span><em>\u00a0<\/em><\/p> <\/td> <\/tr> <tr> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><em>Transitive<\/em><\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0fb1\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f72\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f50\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b<\/span><\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\">\u00a0<\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f63\u0f9f<\/span>\u0f0b \u201cLook\u201d<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f49\u0f53<\/span>\u0f0b \u201cListen\u201d<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0f5f\u0f7c\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cMake\u201d<\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f58\u0f50\u0f7c\u0f44<\/span>\u0f0b \u201cSee\u201d<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f7c\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cHear\u201d<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f67\u0f0b\u0f42<\/span>\u0f7c\u0f0b \u201cUnderstand\u201d<\/p> <\/td> <\/tr> <tr> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><em>Intransitive<\/em><\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f56\u0fb1\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f72\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f50\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b<\/span><\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f49\u0f63\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cLie down\u201d<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f63\u0f44\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cGet up\u201d<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f60\u0f42\u0fb2\u0f7c\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cGo\u201d<\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"192\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f53<\/span>\u0f0b \u201cBe sick\u201d<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f64\u0f72\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cDie\u201d<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"